Online Resources (outside the Library of Congress)
Chicago Fire Chicago Historical Society A city website with information and accounts of the great fire.
The Lost City! A nineteenth century online book describing the Chicago fire.
San Francisco Earthquake Jack London's Eyewitness Account of the San Francisco Earthquake Jack London's description written as a newspaper correspondent.
Museum of the City of San Francisco City site contains information on the 1906 earthquake.
Titanic Encyclopedia Titanica Website containing extensive information on the Titanic including passenger lists and additional website sources.
Johnstown Flood Johnstown Flood Memorial National Park Service site.
Johnstown Flood Museum City site about the flood.
The Dust Bowl The American Experience: The Dust Bowl PBS program site.
1918 Influenza Epidemic The American Experience: Influenza! PBS program site.
Blizzard of 1888 Disposing of Snow An 1888 article about city snow removal.
The Great White Hurricane Description of one of the worst storms on the East Coast.
Galveston Hurricane Extreme Weather NOAA's site about the Galveston hurricane.
Galveston's Home Page City site with information about the storm of 1900.
Peshtigo Fire Peshtigo Fire Historical Society of Wisconsin site.
Reverend Peter Pernin's Account Eyewitness account of the fire.
Wisconsin's Fire A nineteenth century online book describing the Peshtigo fire.
